- Made hollidase sauce for breakfast. I used a powder that worked fine until I added all the
recommended water. The it thinned out and started to separate. I saved it by heating an egg
yoke with a pinch of salt and a tiny bit of water and white wine vinegar heating it until it
started to thinken, then stirring in some of the sauce. This took two attempts because the
yoke cooked the first time

- I made poached eggs with smoked salmon. I smoked the salmon at 85C to an internal temp of 60C
then initiating the shutdown cycle on the smoker. I reasoned that this would hold the salmon at 
60C for 12 minutes, which is the FDA recommendation. The fish was reasonably moist

- Making a beef stock in the instant pot. I used two bone in beef shanks. Browned on the sauté
setting, then cooked on the "stock" setting (30 min at high pressure), with natural venting. I
also added an onion cut in 8ths, salt, and about a cup of frozen chicken stock. Added water to
cover
